    <script type="text/javascript">
        $(document).ready(function() {
            $('.select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').hide();
            
            $('.tab', '#section6').click(function() {
                $('.tab, .tab-content', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $(this).addClass('current');
                $('.tab-content[data-id=' + $(this).data('id') + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($(this).index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').addClass('current');
                chkContentHeight();
            });

            $('.tab-select', '#section6').change(function() {
                $('.tab, .tab-content', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab[data-id=' + $(this).val() + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-content[data-id=' + $(this).val() + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div:nth-child(' +  ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.select .select-container div', '#section6').show();
                $('.select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').hide();
                chkContentHeight();
            });

            $('.record-slider', '#section6').Slider({
                slides: '.record-item',
                maxSlide: 1,
                swipeControl: true,
                skipBoundary: true,
                infiniteLoop: true
            });

            function chkContentHeight() {
                $('p.description', '#section6').each(function() {
                    if($(this).height() > 160) {
                        $(this).parent().addClass('more');
                    }
                });
            }
            chkContentHeight();

            $('.record-item article button.view-more', '#section6').click(function() {
                $(this).hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.view-less').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.description').hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.content').show();
            });
            $('.record-item article button.view-less', '#section6').click(function() {
                $(this).hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.view-more').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.description').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.content').hide();
            });
        });
    </script>
</section>
<section id="section7" data-total="10">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
            <h2 class="colour2">What's New at WIS?</h2>
            <span class="bg-colour1"></span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="record-slider">
        <div class="slider-container">
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="196">
                        <time>19/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Quoi de neuf cette semaine? It’s Francophonie Week at West Island School, and our students are fully immersed in activities celebrating French‑speaking cultures. <br><br>Through games, workshops, crêpe‑making, movie screenings, and singing, they are developing their communication skills, creativity, collaboration and cultural awareness while discovering fun ways of learning a language. @francophonie_hk <br><br>#IBFrench #IBLearnerProfile #internationalschoolshk</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/11fb52dd3875965b6cf23b70bc830896.jpg" alt="653922692_2259291637929842_1753656620327826942_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="195">
                        <time>17/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Last Saturday, our campus was buzzing with energy as we welcomed students, families, alumni and the wider ESF community to our annual WIS Bazaar. It was a joy to see everyone come together for a fantastic family day filled with laughter, connection and school spirit. The atmosphere was truly electric, reminding us of the incredible bond we share across the ESF network.<br><br>The day was a spectacular showcase of our students’ diverse talents and entrepreneurial spirit. A huge well done to our gifted musicians and dancers for their high-energy performances, and a special congratulations to our student filmmakers who screened their original movies for the school community. We were also delighted to welcome students from @esfkennedyschool , who joined us on stage to help spread joy and excitement throughout the day.<br><br>Beyond the stage, our students took the lead in the bustling marketplace. The student-led booths were a major highlight, showcasing impressive creativity, teamwork, and leadership. From interactive games and innovative crafts to thoughtful service-led initiatives, these booths added a unique and vibrant layer to the Bazaar, demonstrating the passion and initiative our students bring to every project.<br><br>Our Technology Faculty and Visual Arts Department were also open to the community, offering a wonderful glimpse into the creative and technical work happening in our classrooms. The conversations between students, parents and teachers were truly inspiring, sparking curiosity and providing a meaningful platform to share the learning journey. Seeing our community engage so deeply with these creative spaces was a testament to the inquisitive spirit of West Island School.<br><br>An event of this scale would not be possible without the immense dedication of our Parent-Teacher Association (PTA). A heartfelt thank you goes out to the PTA Committee and our tireless parent and staff volunteers who worked behind the scenes to bring this wonderful event to life. Their commitment is the driving force of our community, and we are so grateful for everything they do to make WIS such a vibrant place to learn and grow.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/55377ee0485c80551c0f8c229fe9d74e.jpg" alt="652775497_18538084495066491_2163214311624276057_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="194">
                        <time>11/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Join us in the auditorium for an exciting lineup of performances that highlight our students’ creativity and passion:<br><br>The event will conclude with a community African Drumming Experience starting at 2.30pm. <br><br>Please find the ticketing link in bio. See you on Saturday.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/d5737a4b46b5a2666c3792afebaeee8e.jpg" alt="649200305_18536585125066491_4282606698529698177_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="193">
                        <time>03/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our Visual Arts space is the perfect creative hub for open-minded inquirers and risk-takers. Students from all year groups bring a shared passion to build community, show compassion, and find the courage to explore their purpose through the grace of art. <br><br>Our dedicated teachers and staff are here to help every student realise their potential. Whether you are starting a fresh project or continuing an unfinished piece, we look forward to seeing you back in the studio tomorrow.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/71118bb9ae57570b4c879fc2295dbece.jpg" alt="642623416_812191098607091_6975225477301782365_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="192">
                        <time>25/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>From athletic strength and sportsmanship to the unbeatable bond between students and staff, our Sports Day truly brought our values of Community, Compassion and Courage to life.<br><br>Check out this video for a recap of the amazing atmosphere.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/52fc9242dac9c815dc885522638a2590.jpg" alt="639895789_18533804467066491_8354145395220908454_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="191">
                        <time>16/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>🐎 Roaring into the Year of the Horse! 🧨<br><br>From mastering Mandarin phrases to the powerful rhythm of the Lion Dance, our students fully immersed themselves in the rich traditions of Chinese language and culture before the half-term holiday. 🏮✨ <br><br>At West Island School, we believe that learning a language is about understanding the heart of a culture. Seeing our students embrace the discipline of the dance and the beauty of the brush has been the perfect way to kick off this festive season.<br><br>West Island School wishes everyone a wonderful New Year of the Horse! May you embody the spirit of the Horse this year—galloping toward your goals with strength, speed, and boundless energy. <br><br>Keep exploring, being curious, and celebrating the diversity of our community.<br><br>Happy Lunar New Year!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/3b31bd47209753cca0688de9f7c28c57.jpg" alt="632800740_925658549904121_3517229643503254854_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="190">
                        <time>13/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>The first half of Term 2 has been an incredibly inspiring start to 2026, filled with moments that truly highlight the spirit of our school community. Watch Mrs Hallatt's update video to look back at what we have achieved together.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/59da7455129e0f49bc9974c448c0c939.jpg" alt="630153971_18529748563066491_5814136640561787058_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="189">
                        <time>13/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>Live at Sports Day! 🏆 It’s more than just a celebration of athletic strength and sportsmanship—it’s about the irreplaceable house and community spirit shared by our students and staff.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/ba6b308d5727ee70e8c040162fe8802e.jpg" alt="632500862_18529737841066491_2559790282235385395_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="188">
                        <time>12/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our WIS Bazaar is still open for commercial vendors to team up with our Parent-Teacher Association (PTA) for a wonderful day celebrating the school community. <br><br>Date: Saturday, 14 March 2026<br>Time: 11am - 4pm<br>Location: West Island School, 250 Victoria Road, Pok Fu Lam<br><br>If you are interested in joining our PTA with a market stall, please find the details and submit your application through the form by scanning the QR code in this post.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/4fc1986844224380fcc70691bb89efc1.jpg" alt="629782775_18529622092066491_4083385733338015223_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="187">
                        <time>04/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>Over the years, our caring and dedicated Parent Teacher Association (PTA) has generously funded a diverse range of items to enrich our learning and school life. <br><br>From music to sports and campus style, here’s a look at what the PTA has provided for our students:<br><br>• Music 🎶: Drum kits, cymbals, bass guitars, amplifiers, and acoustic guitars <br>• Table Tennis 🏓 : New table for break-time fun <br>Sports Hall 🕰️: New large clock and timer to keep us on track <br>• Campus Life 🪑 🌬️: Cafeteria furniture, a vibrant school mural, and swamp fans to keep us cool! <br>• Tech 💡🖥️ : Auditorium insights, light diffusion kits, and digital signage displays <br><br>A huge thank you to our PTA for creating these wonderful opportunities. They’ve also promised us an unforgettable WIS Bazaar on 14 March, from 11am to 4pm! See you and your families there!<br><br>#schoolcommunity #schoollife #studentwellbeing</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/93ace2b2932204e8a703559aaba7810d.jpg" alt="627942639_18527020921066491_8070044904132490535_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="196">
                        <time>19/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Quoi de neuf cette semaine? It’s Francophonie Week at West Island School, and our students are fully immersed in activities celebrating French‑speaking cultures. <br><br>Through games, workshops, crêpe‑making, movie screenings, and singing, they are developing their communication skills, creativity, collaboration and cultural awareness while discovering fun ways of learning a language. @francophonie_hk <br><br>#IBFrench #IBLearnerProfile #internationalschoolshk</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/11fb52dd3875965b6cf23b70bc830896.jpg" alt="653922692_2259291637929842_1753656620327826942_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="195">
                        <time>17/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Last Saturday, our campus was buzzing with energy as we welcomed students, families, alumni and the wider ESF community to our annual WIS Bazaar. It was a joy to see everyone come together for a fantastic family day filled with laughter, connection and school spirit. The atmosphere was truly electric, reminding us of the incredible bond we share across the ESF network.<br><br>The day was a spectacular showcase of our students’ diverse talents and entrepreneurial spirit. A huge well done to our gifted musicians and dancers for their high-energy performances, and a special congratulations to our student filmmakers who screened their original movies for the school community. We were also delighted to welcome students from @esfkennedyschool , who joined us on stage to help spread joy and excitement throughout the day.<br><br>Beyond the stage, our students took the lead in the bustling marketplace. The student-led booths were a major highlight, showcasing impressive creativity, teamwork, and leadership. From interactive games and innovative crafts to thoughtful service-led initiatives, these booths added a unique and vibrant layer to the Bazaar, demonstrating the passion and initiative our students bring to every project.<br><br>Our Technology Faculty and Visual Arts Department were also open to the community, offering a wonderful glimpse into the creative and technical work happening in our classrooms. The conversations between students, parents and teachers were truly inspiring, sparking curiosity and providing a meaningful platform to share the learning journey. Seeing our community engage so deeply with these creative spaces was a testament to the inquisitive spirit of West Island School.<br><br>An event of this scale would not be possible without the immense dedication of our Parent-Teacher Association (PTA). A heartfelt thank you goes out to the PTA Committee and our tireless parent and staff volunteers who worked behind the scenes to bring this wonderful event to life. Their commitment is the driving force of our community, and we are so grateful for everything they do to make WIS such a vibrant place to learn and grow.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/55377ee0485c80551c0f8c229fe9d74e.jpg" alt="652775497_18538084495066491_2163214311624276057_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="194">
                        <time>11/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Join us in the auditorium for an exciting lineup of performances that highlight our students’ creativity and passion:<br><br>The event will conclude with a community African Drumming Experience starting at 2.30pm. <br><br>Please find the ticketing link in bio. See you on Saturday.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/d5737a4b46b5a2666c3792afebaeee8e.jpg" alt="649200305_18536585125066491_4282606698529698177_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="193">
                        <time>03/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our Visual Arts space is the perfect creative hub for open-minded inquirers and risk-takers. Students from all year groups bring a shared passion to build community, show compassion, and find the courage to explore their purpose through the grace of art. <br><br>Our dedicated teachers and staff are here to help every student realise their potential. Whether you are starting a fresh project or continuing an unfinished piece, we look forward to seeing you back in the studio tomorrow.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/71118bb9ae57570b4c879fc2295dbece.jpg" alt="642623416_812191098607091_6975225477301782365_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="192">
                        <time>25/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>From athletic strength and sportsmanship to the unbeatable bond between students and staff, our Sports Day truly brought our values of Community, Compassion and Courage to life.<br><br>Check out this video for a recap of the amazing atmosphere.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/52fc9242dac9c815dc885522638a2590.jpg" alt="639895789_18533804467066491_8354145395220908454_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="191">
                        <time>16/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>🐎 Roaring into the Year of the Horse! 🧨<br><br>From mastering Mandarin phrases to the powerful rhythm of the Lion Dance, our students fully immersed themselves in the rich traditions of Chinese language and culture before the half-term holiday. 🏮✨ <br><br>At West Island School, we believe that learning a language is about understanding the heart of a culture. Seeing our students embrace the discipline of the dance and the beauty of the brush has been the perfect way to kick off this festive season.<br><br>West Island School wishes everyone a wonderful New Year of the Horse! May you embody the spirit of the Horse this year—galloping toward your goals with strength, speed, and boundless energy. <br><br>Keep exploring, being curious, and celebrating the diversity of our community.<br><br>Happy Lunar New Year!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
